# Keep secrets and build junk out of the image build context.
#
# NOTE ON SCOPE: the backend and frontend builds use the REPOSITORY ROOT as their
# build context (docker build -f infra/docker/Dockerfile.* .). A .dockerignore is
# read from the context root, so this file only takes effect for builds whose
# context is infra/docker itself. The Dockerfiles do not rely on it: each COPYs an
# explicit allowlist of paths (gradle/build-logic/backend, or frontend sources), so
# no secret can reach a layer even if a pattern here is missed. This file documents
# the excluded-inputs contract and trims the context when infra/docker IS the root.

# --- Secrets — never in an image (this repo is public) ----------------------
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
**/*.pem
**/secrets/
**/*.tfstate
**/*.tfstate.*
**/*.tfvars

# --- Build outputs & caches — never needed in an image ----------------------
.git
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.angular
**/build
**/.gradle
**/out-tsc
**/coverage
**/playwright-report
**/test-results

# --- Local noise ------------------------------------------------------------
**/.DS_Store
**/*.log
**/.idea
**/.vscode
